    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="176"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1774</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Group</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>23 <hi rend="smallcaps">Wall Street</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your letter to us of April 5 last,
                    in which you advised us that you were giving consideration to the matter of a
                    proposal for a supplementary Reorganization Loan to the Chinese <pb facs="0296"
                        n="130" xml:id="pg_130"/> Government, and would inform us later of the
                    Department’s opinion relative thereto, we would state that we have now received
                    the following cable from our London house: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Your 2003. In view of termination Sextuple Agreement 18th June and
                            possible complications arising thereafter Addis would personally greatly
                            appreciate expression your views as to likelihood of Administration
                            authorizing Group to undertake proposed advance.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>We would greatly appreciate any expression of opinion which you may find it
                    convenient to give us on this subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The American Group</hi>, <lb/> By <hi rend="smallcaps">J.
                        P. Morgan</hi> &amp; Co.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
